---
import Layout from '@layouts/Layout.astro';
import Navbar from '@components/Navbar/Navbar.astro';
import SplitReveal from '@components/SplitReveal/SplitReveal.astro';
import Button from '@components/Button/Button.astro';
import { Picture } from 'astro:assets';

import header from '@images/mobiletire.png';
import Footer from '@components/Footer/Footer.astro';

import img1 from '@images/36-products-3.jpg';
import img2 from '@images/36-shelf.jpg';
import img3 from '@images/36-social.jpg';
---

<Layout title="ISEAD">
    <div class="relative flex flex-col">
        <div class="fixed top-0 right-0 left-0 z-50 h-fit bg-black">
            <Navbar />
        </div>
        <div
            class="relative grid h-fit w-full grid-cols-12 gap-fluid-twenty bg-white pt-36 pr-fluid-twenty pb-fluid-eighty pl-fluid-twenty sm:pb-fluid-270"
        >
            <div
                class="col-span-12 flex h-fit flex-col gap-4 self-start text-body-md leading-[110%] tracking-[-2%] sm:sticky sm:top-24 sm:col-span-4 3xl:col-span-3"
            >
                <div class="pb-fluid-eighty md:pb-0">
                    <h1>Thirty6Xposures</h1>
                    <h2 class="text-[#3e3e3e]">Product Sourcing, Event</h2>
                </div>
                <div class="flex flex-row justify-start">
                    <a class="hover-underline w-fit text-body-sm tracking-[-1%]"
                        >See all projects ↗</a
                    >
                </div>
                <div
                    class="desktop-version flex flex-col gap-fluid-twenty bg-[#EEEEEE] p-fluid-thirty text-body-project leading-[120%] tracking-[-2%] text-[#3e3e3e]"
                >
                    <h4 class="pb-fluid-twenty text-body-sm">Project Description</h4>
                    <p>
                        A prominent Toronto-based photographer created the thirty6Xposures
                        Photography Challenge & Documentary Film. With Season 1 complete and Season
                        2 underway, the producer wanted a thoughtful gift to thank the featured
                        photographers and crew. The gift needed to be practical for everyday use
                        on-brand with 36X’s signature yellow, stay within budget, and offer a
                        distinctive and meaningful touch.
                    </p>

                    <p>
                        After selecting a tumbler as the gift, We found the Asobu Orb from Adnart—a
                        standout yellow option whose unique shape subtly echoed a Kodak film
                        canister, perfectly nodding to the photography theme. We used a
                        clean,1-colour black logo imprint and utilized the Orb's bold yellow to
                        represent the second logo color and maintain a tight imprint cost. Paired
                        with an existing 36X-branded black trucker hat, the gift kit was both
                        functional and visually impactful. The target audience included the eight
                        featured photographers, crew, affiliates and general public.
                    </p>
                    <p>
                        On the first day of gathering, the gifts were bestowed upon all 36X members,
                        including the crew and the eight featured photographers. The moment served
                        not just as a gesture of appreciation, but also as a unifying kickoff to the
                        project. The vibrant yellow Orbs became a treasured reminder of the 36X
                        experience. Used on set, after filming, and shared on social media, even
                        featured in documentary footage!
                    </p>
                    <p>
                        Beyond their practical use, the tumblers served as conversation starters,
                        thanks to their clear branding and high visibility throughout the weekend of
                        filming and in the daily routines of those who received them. This exposure
                        has sparked interest from other photographers eager to apply for future
                        seasons, along with inquiries from potential sponsors and media partners.
                        One standout moment includes an opportunity for conversation with a
                        prominent Toronto-based multimedia outlet, expressing interest in how they
                        can be part of distribution or sponsorship!
                    </p>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div
                class="mob-version col-span-12 flex flex-col gap-fluid-twenty bg-[#EEEEEE] px-fluid-forty pt-fluid-forty pb-fluid-eighty text-body-project leading-[120%] tracking-[-2%] text-[#3e3e3e]"
            >
                <h4 class="pb-fluid-160 text-body-sm">Project Description</h4>
                <p>
                    A prominent Toronto-based photographer created the thirty6Xposures Photography
                    Challenge & Documentary Film. With Season 1 complete and Season 2 underway, the
                    producer wanted a thoughtful gift to thank the featured photographers and crew.
                    The gift needed to be practical for everyday use on-brand with 36X’s signature
                    yellow, stay within budget, and offer a distinctive and meaningful touch.
                </p>

                <p>
                    After selecting a tumbler as the gift, We found the Asobu Orb from Adnart—a
                    standout yellow option whose unique shape subtly echoed a Kodak film canister,
                    perfectly nodding to the photography theme. We used a clean,1-colour black logo
                    imprint and utilized the Orb's bold yellow to represent the second logo color
                    and maintain a tight imprint cost. Paired with an existing 36X-branded black
                    trucker hat, the gift kit was both functional and visually impactful. The target
                    audience included the eight featured photographers, crew, affiliates and general
                    public.
                </p>
                <p>
                    On the first day of gathering, the gifts were bestowed upon all 36X members,
                    including the crew and the eight featured photographers. The moment served not
                    just as a gesture of appreciation, but also as a unifying kickoff to the
                    project. The vibrant yellow Orbs became a treasured reminder of the 36X
                    experience. Used on set, after filming, and shared on social media, even
                    featured in documentary footage!
                </p>
                <p>
                    Beyond their practical use, the tumblers served as conversation starters, thanks
                    to their clear branding and high visibility throughout the weekend of filming
                    and in the daily routines of those who received them. This exposure has sparked
                    interest from other photographers eager to apply for future seasons, along with
                    inquiries from potential sponsors and media partners. One standout moment
                    includes an opportunity for conversation with a prominent Toronto-based
                    multimedia outlet, expressing interest in how they can be part of distribution
                    or sponsorship!
                </p>
            </div>
            <div
                class="col-span-12 flex w-full flex-col gap-fluid-twenty sm:col-span-8 3xl:col-span-9"
            >
                <Picture src={img1} alt="ISEAD Awards" class="h-auto w-full" loading="lazy" />
                <Picture src={img2} alt="ISEAD Awards" class="h-auto w-full" loading="lazy" />
                <Picture src={img3} alt="ISEAD Group Photo" class="h-auto w-full" loading="lazy" />
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
    <Footer />
</Layout>
